Business Brief -- Midlantic Corp.:
   Banking Affiliates Are Sold
   For Total of $219 Million
Midlantic also sold United Penn Bank, with assets of $1.5
billion and based in Wilkes-Barre, Pa., to Mellon Bank,
Pittsburgh, for $90 million. United Penn operates 33 offices
in six Pennsylvania counties. Mellon Bank is a subsidiary of
Mellon Bank Corp.
   As previously announced, the sales are part of a plan to
bolster Midlantic's capital and improve capital adequacy
ratios.